    <item>
      <title>15.08 Peonies and Roses (1)</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/15-08-peonies-and-roses-1/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/15-08-peonies-and-roses-1/</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 20 May 2026 13:54:43 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main id="wp--skip-link--target" class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;15.08 Peonies and Roses&amp;nbsp;(1)&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/15-07-baby-deer-baby-boar-baby-bear-3/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;That day, Court Physician Liu came over to Maomao’s section with a grave expression.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I have something to talk to you about after work,” he said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao found herself on guard by how meekly he was speaking to her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Hey, what did you do?” “It must be really serious to have Court Physician Liu come in person.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Court Physician Ri and Wanwan-senpai spoke in unison.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I-I didn’t do anything?” Maomao said. &lt;em&gt;Pretty sure I didn’t&lt;/em&gt;, she thought back on her actions the last couple of days. The bear gallbladder she got back from the hunter had been processed properly in the medical office. She had not pocketed it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I’ve no idea what you did, but I can testify that the medical office inventory is correct. I know you didn’t touch anything there.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Looks like Wanwan-senpai would cover for Maomao in his own way. By the sounds of it, he wanted to say that she hadn’t been embezzling at the very least. Additionally, the medicine inventory was managed by the two of them, so there would be joint liability should any dishonesty come to light.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;It would be a pain if Tianyu were here, but thankfully, he was out today. No doubt he would be cackling and spreading the news like a cat that caught the canary.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;After work, Maomao headed over to Court Physician Liu’s office.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Excuse me.” She cautiously opened the door.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Court Physician Liu was facing off a calendar with a grave expression. “Now you’re here,” he said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“What do you need me for?” she asked, rubbing her hands lightly.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I have a question for you.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Yes.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“You are very familiar with the Verdigris Mansion, yes?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Yes, very much so.” Calling it her home wouldn’t be an exaggeration.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Then, are you familiar with the Gold Thread Pavilion?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Ahh.” Maomao figured out the reason Court Physician Liu summoned her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;As a show of appreciation, officials would hold their own banquets near the end of the year. On these occasions, it wouldn’t be unusual for them to use high-class brothels. People of high status, in particular, would know someone’s preferences by the type of shop chosen.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The Gold Thread Pavilion was a long-standing brothel like the Verdigris Mansion—in simple terms, they were business rivals.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Does this mean that the venue for the end-of-year drinks has yet to be picked?” she asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“The venue is set. The wine and food are set too. However, our responsibility this year is to decide on the women from which shop. It’s &lt;em&gt;such &lt;/em&gt;a hassle.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Going by how he worded it as &lt;em&gt;our responsibility&lt;/em&gt;, it would have to be a joint banquet with other departments.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Wouldn’t it be better to leave such a task to your subordinates?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;A person of Court Physician Liu’s ranking shouldn’t be acting as the coordinator&lt;/em&gt;, Maomao thought.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“We’ve previously left it to them, but we were ultimately shown to a cheap, promising, and rowdy shop on the streets. We got swarmed by teahouse girls.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“So it had been inappropriate.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Indeed, it had been. It led to a grave problem at the time, and from then on, the responsibility fell onto the department head to manage it all.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Woaah.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao could imagine. Court Physician Liu was fussing over it, which meant that the banquet had people of his status or higher attending as well.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Um, were you okay?” she asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“How could I have been? However, it was thanks to a certain person that the incident didn’t end with the subordinates’ heads rolling.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“That person must have been quite commendable.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Not at all. Let’s say that the problem stemmed from that very person. From the very beginning, without even touching a drop of wine, he sent all sorts of things flying and partially destroyed the shop. If this had been a high-class establishment, it would have all been glossed over.” &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“….”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao didn’t need to question who on earth that person was. A monocled figure with eyes like a fox came to mind.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Moreover, that person doesn’t get called anymore. His position became one that didn’t need to be invited.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Curiously, this became an issue where low-level grunts do not invite a high-ranking official.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“So that’s why,” she said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“So please give me an answer for the Verdigris Mansion without any reservations. Which of the two shops is better?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“You ask me, but I’m nothing more than a supporting role at the Verdigris Mansion. There are many restaurants besides brothels as well. More importantly, I am no longer sure if you can make a reservation on your preferred date. If it’s the Verdigris Mansion, well, they’ll make all the accommodations you want if you put in a deposit.” The madam’s scary face flashed in her mind. The old woman had told her to bring in lots of rich customers while waving her pipe around.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao thought about it.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;It’s a pain. Let’s sell out the madam and charge a brokerage fee while I’m at it.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;She heard the cackling of a little demon.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;I should respond sincerely for the sake of the future.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;She heard the admonishing voice of a celestial maiden.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“If you can get me the plan and the quote, I’ll bring you along to buy herbal medicines this time.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Understood!” Maomao firmed up her expression and straightened her posture.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;After parting ways with Court Physician Liu, Maomao immediately headed to the pleasure district.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Um, the high officials attending, where it’s held, and the plan…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;These details would be more secret under normal circumstances, but she supposed that he trusted her to a certain extent.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ah, this place.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao recognised it. It was where she had her part-time job after leaving the inner palace. She remembered there being a Jinshi who had been withdrawn.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;I guess we’re stuck together now, for better or worse.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Since she had been there before, the details were easy to imagine: the size and structure of the room, a good number of courtesans, and so on and so forth.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Oh, Maomao,” Ukyou called out to her. “Sazen isn’t here today. He went out to buy medicine.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I don’t have business with Sazen. Is Gran here?” she asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Gran? She just went to the meeting.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“The meeting.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;In a way, it was convenient.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;In a way, it was not.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The pleasure district was not composed of a single shop. The shop owners would regularly convene to discuss and decide on matters of the pleasure district—things like sweeping the main street, gatekeeper rotations, cleaning the outer moat, and so on and so forth. They would also rein in the shops that use extreme prices to lure in customers.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The Verdigris Mansion was one of the three major shops in the pleasure district.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The Gold Thread Pavilion was another one of the three.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Could she consider it great timing that they were having their discussions at the same time?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ideally, I would like to get the quotes separately.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;However, Maomao also had work tomorrow. She wanted to get this over and done with.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Will it be okay?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Feeling uneasy, Maomao headed to the meeting place.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;sub&gt;T/N: &lt;s&gt;Will me posting this chapter summon the next chapter? &lt;/s&gt;🤞&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right wp-block-paragraph"&gt;(Next Chapter)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/15-08-peonies-and-roses-1/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-5678-6a467fbe72c4d' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20260702#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=5678&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-5678-6a467fbe72c4d' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-5678-6a467fbe72c4d' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/15-08-peonies-and-roses-1/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
