    <item>
      <title>15.07 Baby Deer, Baby Boar, Baby Bear (3)</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/15-07-baby-deer-baby-boar-baby-bear-3/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/15-07-baby-deer-baby-boar-baby-bear-3/</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 06:25:12 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main id="wp--skip-link--target" class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;15.07 Baby Deer, Baby Boar, Baby Bear&amp;nbsp;(3)&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/15-06-baby-deer-baby-boar-baby-bear-2/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;sup&gt;T/N: Bear gall (熊胆) refers to the TCM name, whereas bear gallbladder (熊の胆のう) refers to the organ itself.&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The next morning, Maomao and the others were roused awake by a villager.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Hey! You’re doctors, aren’t you? Follow me!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;It was the hunter who had led them to the unoccupied house the day before.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;What is this about?&lt;/em&gt; Maomao thought as she rubbed her eyes while getting up from her bed.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“What is the matter?” Changsha, being the most junior, responded. Yao was looking dazedly at the ceiling.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao quickly changed out of her clothes.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“We have a sick person. Please examine them,” the hunter said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“…” Changsha turned to look at Maomao for directions.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“…What are their symptoms, age, and gender?” Maomao took over from Changsha after she put on a thick jacket.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“It’s my son. He’s only five. He has a headache and has been vomiting since last night.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Please show me the way.” Maomao decided to head over first and have the others join her later once they were done changing. “Wouldn’t it be better to ask the other doctors?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I did, but they turned me down. They told me that I’d be better off asking you guys.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Huh.” Wanwan-senpai would be happy to take on the job, but he was probably still asleep. She figured that the other court physicians had made the call without asking him.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“It’s this house,” the hunter said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;They went inside. A child was lying on a worn bed. A woman, who seemed to be the child’s mother, was carrying a wooden tub. She looked exhausted and listless.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Could it be malnutrition?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;They looked strangely impoverished.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Please allow me to examine him.” Maomao looked into the wooden tub. There was the sour stench of vomit, but there were barely any solids. “What did he eat last night?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Congee and soup.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Did the two of you eat the same thing?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“We did.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I will check the pot, okay?” Maomao headed over to the stove. The crude pot had what seemed to be root vegetables and small flecks of meat floating in it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Bear meat?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;It was neither chicken nor pork. Although it resembled beef, the fact that they were in a village of hunters made it more reasonable that it was bear.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Had they processed yesterday’s bear already?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao used a bamboo ladle to scoop up some of the cold soup and put it in her mouth.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ah?!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao gulped it down, then looked at the villager, the woman and the weakened child.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;She understood why the woman looked oddly impoverished. Her skin was lax, and her hair was thin with no lustre at all.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The child looked even worse. In comparison, the villager didn’t look that bad.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Maomao, is there anything you need?” Yao asked, turning up late with Changsha.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao slowly shook her head, instead presenting the soup to the two of them.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“What’s this?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Soup. Take a guess at what it’s made from.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Yao hesitated, but when she saw Changsha directly use the bamboo ladle to try the soup, she followed. “…Hm, it tastes richer than it looks, doesn’t it?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“It’s not salty, but thanks to that, it has a depth to it, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Could this be ground liver?” Yao ventured. “There is a gamey flavour and some grittiness to it.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Correct.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Then Maomao recalled what she had wanted to steal back from the hunter. The three of them looked at the hunter.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Yesterday, you brought back bear fur, meat and some of its organs as well, right? You said that it was your cousin who did it, and you know nothing about it, but then why is &lt;em&gt;that &lt;/em&gt;in your pot? Bear liver.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The hunter averted his eyes awkwardly. “…My bad. It’s because I’m a poor hunter that we rarely get meat allocated to us. You can tell by looking at the soup—the meat is basically nothing but shreds and sinew.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“So you added liver.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Yeah. It spoils quickly and has a strong flavour, but it’s better than eating nothing.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Are you unable to hunt any animals?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Unlike my cousins, I am bad at hunting.” The hunter slowly added to the story. He spoke about how hunting was the village’s livelihood, and that they often hunted in groups since they were related. Those with higher contributions got better cuts and bigger portions of the meat.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Organs are cheap because they spoil quickly.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Do you regularly eat the liver?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Yeah. My son can’t stomach the other parts, but for liver, if we dissolve it into the soup, he’ll eat it.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao nodded in understanding. Yao and Changsha looked at Maomao curiously.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I know the cause of his illness. It has to be because of the bear liver,” Maomao said, pointing to the pot on the stove.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Hold on. We eat it all the time. Why is it a problem now?” the hunter asked.&lt;br&gt;Yao and Changsha looked at her for an explanation as well.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Bear liver is highly nutritious, but are you aware that too much nutrition isn’t good for you?” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I hear that often,” Changsha replied. “Things that are nutritious in small amounts, but become poisonous when you take too much. Bear liver is the same. Eating it once or twice normally wouldn’t get you sick from it. But what happens if you keep eating too much of it over a long period of time, like almost every day? Wouldn’t it accumulate in your body?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao looked at the hunter’s impoverished-looking wife. She looked oddly aged due to her thin hair and rough skin. “An example I know of it is eating too much eel. Eel is highly nutritious and energising, but I’ve heard that eating too much will harm you.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Ah, in that case,” Yao raised her hand. “This is something I heard from En’en a long time ago. There’s a story about someone getting food poisoning from eating the innards of a bear from the far north as a delicacy. I always thought it was due to food spoilage.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao listened carefully as well. She would ask En’en for further details once they got back.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&amp;#8220;Then, I ate it daily too. Why am &lt;em&gt;I&lt;/em&gt; okay?” the hunter asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Isn’t it simply because of size differences?” Maomao asked him back. “From now on, it would be better to cut down on eating animal liver. Please work harder on hunting.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Although it was a harsh thing to say, that was all Maomao could offer him.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Also,” Maomao looked at the kitchen restlessly. “Did the liver come with a gallbladder?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“If it’s that…” the hunter pointed at the bin. “We tossed it.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“WHAT A WASTE!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Before getting to him being bad at hunting, he didn’t know the value of things either.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao panicked, lifted the lid of the waste bin, and started to rummage through it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“THAT’S FILTHY!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Yao got mad at her, but Maomao searched for the gallbladder without a care.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Hahaha, bear gall.” Head covered in vegetable scraps, Maomao raised the soaked bear gallbladder high into the air.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-center wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“&lt;em&gt;Baby bear, baby bear,&lt;br&gt;Little baby bear.&lt;br&gt;Drink lots of milk, eat lots of acorns,&lt;br&gt;And once you grow big, run far, far away.&lt;br&gt;Baby bear, baby bear,&lt;br&gt;Little baby bear.&lt;/em&gt;”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao heard someone singing when she returned to the medical office in the imperial court. It was Tianyu.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Oh, welcome baaack,” he said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I’m back,” she said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao found it more important to deal with the gallbladder she received over Tianyu’s song, but he came over to talk to her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“That was the third verse of the song we spoke about before.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Yes, I just heard it.” Maomao looked for a spot to dry the gallbladder she had wiped down nicely.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I’ve mentioned that the lyrics were about running away from the bear, but it varies depending on the locality. I just sang a different version of the song.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Yeah, sure,” Maomao replied without taking a break.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-center wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“&lt;em&gt;Baby bear, baby bear,&lt;br&gt;Little baby bear.&lt;br&gt;Drink lots of milk, eat lots of acorns,&lt;br&gt;And once you grow big, run far, far away.&lt;br&gt;Baby bear, baby bear,&lt;br&gt;Little baby bear.&lt;/em&gt;”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The baby bear would be a bear cub.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“What do you think giving it milk and acorns means?” Tianyu asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Beats me. Could it be that it’s bad to feed wild animals?” she asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“No, no. It’s about owning the cubs.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Owning?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Like raising it. Not hunting.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao hung up the gallbladder at the perfect spot, then looked at Tianyu.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“They hunt down the mother bear, leaving behind the bear cub. The cub is still too small to be eaten, so they raise it.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Giving them milk and feed in place of the mother bear.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Then they eat it before it becomes an adult.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Huuuh.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Bears, unlike when they’re small, are scary when they grow into adults, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Is there a punchline to it?” Maomao caressed the suspended gallbladder.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Not at all. Just that I remembered that bears eat people and are also eaten by people.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Is that so? Next time, tell me something more interesting, please.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“If you found that boring, that’s unfortunate.” Tianyu spread his hands and left.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;He probably wanted to leave a snide remark. That’s the type of person he was.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;I would choose to be the one eating.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;But when faced with reality, Maomao would be the one being eaten.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The gallbladder had delighted her, but it was no doubt something the hunters had put their lives on the line to obtain.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;That hunter who was bad at hunting had also put his life on the line to work. But since he couldn’t sufficiently acquire meat, he couldn’t sufficiently feed his family well.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;He doesn’t know how bear gall is made.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;If he had known, he would have probably lived a little better. That being said, if she were to tell him the processing method, he could sell it to them at a high price when he comes to the medical office.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;While Maomao considered herself heartless for not teaching him, she could never spread that information. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;She wasn’t a good person who could be nice to everyone. After all, the number of people she could extend a helping hand to only amounted to what she could count on two hands.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right wp-block-paragraph"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/15-08-peonies-and-roses-1/"&gt;Next chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/15-07-baby-deer-baby-boar-baby-bear-3/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-5656-6a467fbe8c397' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20260702#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=5656&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-5656-6a467fbe8c397' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-5656-6a467fbe8c397' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/15-07-baby-deer-baby-boar-baby-bear-3/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
