      <title>15.06 Baby Deer, Baby Boar, Baby Bear (2)</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/15-06-baby-deer-baby-boar-baby-bear-2/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/15-06-baby-deer-baby-boar-baby-bear-2/</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 31 Dec 2025 08:45:40 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main id="wp--skip-link--target" class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;15.06 Baby Deer, Baby Boar, Baby Bear&amp;nbsp;(2)&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/15-05-baby-deer-baby-boar-baby-bear-1/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Wanwan-senpai looked at the organs that had been laid out and made a sour face. “They agreed to leave us the gallbladder, did they not?” he said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao wasn’t happy either. “Shall we go and get it back from them right now?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The gallbladder of a bear was the ingredient for bear’s gall. If anything, Maomao could say that the bear was primarily dissected for that part.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Maomao, why would you need a knife to get back the gallbladder?” he asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao quickly hid the small dissection knife.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“We were talking about lodgings, weren’t we?” he then said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Yes, it sounds like they have arranged two rooms for us, a large one and a small one,” she answered.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Although they had no idea what the rooms would be like, they probably wouldn’t be shown to the stables, considering the sum of money the court physicians handed over to the hunters as recompensation.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“As much as I would like us to go right this instant, the dissection comes first,” he said&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“We can’t go right now?” she asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“We can’t.”&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Wanwan-senpai went on to identify the entrails while giving an explanation to the junior court physicians. A pale-faced Yao studied the organ parts with teary eyes.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;You’re better off quitting if it’s not for you.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;It was Yao’s weakness not to do so, but it was also her strength. Perhaps what Changsha had told her previously had left quite the impression on her, seeing as Yao had returned to her family home.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;And speaking of Changsha…&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Excuse me, can this be eaten later?” the junior asked while looking at the bear entrails.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“When the entrails aren’t fresh, they have a strong stench and can’t be eaten,” Maomao replied.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Changsha’s brows drooped in disappointment. “Not even with ginger?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“It’s because we don’t know what the wild bears have eaten,” Maomao said honestly. Apparently, human hair had been discovered in a bear dissected in the past.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“That might be quite unpleasant.” Changsha had quite the nerves of steel.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;No wonder she’s been called over.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Before Maomao could join in with the other court physicians on dissections, she had been faced with various issues. The biggest of those was that there was no precedent.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Conversely, now that there was a precedent, it was probably easy to have Changsha participate.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;When they finished examining the bear’s organs, they processed the useful parts. There was bear’s gall, a medicine sourced from bears, but its other parts also had uses.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I wonder if they could spare us some bear fat,” a court physician with relatively practiced hands said. He wasn’t a first timer, having participated several times before.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“We had no agreement to obtain fat, but why do you ask?” Wanwan-senpai asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“It’s nothing much. I just heard that applying it to your hair will help with hair growth.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Really?” Wanwan-senpai was also interested.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;It seems that when gentlemen pass a certain age, they end up becoming creatures concerned about their hair.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao splashed water onto the boulder after they had dealt with the innards. She scrubbed away at the smeared blood as she rinsed it off. It was so cold that her fingers were numb.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Ugh.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Yao and Changsha did the same, scrubbing away with straw. Yao’s hands were chapped. No matter how much she moisturised, her hands were bound to end up like that if she was washing up every single day.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“You guys, wash up properly as well,” Wanwan-senpai said to the new court physicians. They joined in.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Among them, some remained sitting, still feeling unwell, and some refused to work, stating that cleaning wasn’t a job for court physicians.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Yao, in her annoyance, was about to call out to the ones who weren’t washing, but Maomao slapped her on the shoulders.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Let’s not,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Why not?” Yao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Wanwan-senpai isn&amp;#8217;t blind.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Yao looked at Wanwan-senpai. As he was here on a teaching role, he had his eye on every detail. He was certainly looking out for the qualities of a court physician, but those who fail to do the work assigned to them would be ruled out. Did they not think that it would affect their future career prospects?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Then, how would he regard Yao?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;You could say that she didn’t have the aptitude for dissections, but would he acknowledge her determination to keep going despite that?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Qualities were important, but an attitude to confront their weakness was even more so. Otherwise, they would end up with good-for-nothings like Tianyu.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“We’ll head to the village once we’re done with cleaning up,” Wanwan-senpai announced.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao rubbed her numb hands as she puffed out a breath of white air.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Please make use of this house.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The hunter guided them to an unoccupied house. It was in pretty good condition, appearing to be the house of a villager who had left recently. There were four rooms, so there was plenty of space for them.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“There is not enough bedding, so please use these as you see fit.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;They were provided with animal furs. It was probably much preferable to sleeping on the prickly dirt floor.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao scowled at the hunter as she nudged Wanwan-senpai.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Wanwan-senpai, getting the message, approached the hunter. “I’m grateful for the rooms, but I would like to chat about the matter of you taking away bear organ parts that differed from what we had agreed on.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“That’d be my younger cousin, not me.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“What?” Wanwan-senpai made a look of surprise. Maomao was surprised too. Was he not the hunter who took away the bear meat just now?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“We’re all relatives in this village. Me and my cousin look alike, so we often get mistaken for one another.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“&amp;#8230;Sorry, you really do look alike,” Wanwan-senpai apologised genuinely. Turns out he wasn’t the hunter from before but another villager.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;But they really do look alike.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Setting Maomao, who wasn’t good at remembering people’s faces, aside, even Wanwan-senpai got confused.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Come to think of it, the person we entrusted to arrange our lodgings looked alike, too.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;The village wasn’t very open, so it might be that everyone was closely related and had similar faces.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“We have food if you want it,” the villager said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“A share per the number of people here, please. It’ll be great if you could up the portions a bit.” Wanwan-senpai passed the villager a pouch of coins.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Got it. Also, please don’t wander around at night. If you get attacked by an animal, no one can save you,” the villager said, then left the house.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“It’s gotten chilly,” Yao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Shall we get a fire going?” Maomao looked at the pile of firewood on the dirt floor. Did the original owners have intentions of returning? There was furniture left behind as well.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Changsha promptly fetched a fire starter, so Maomao prepared the straw.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I’ll go draw water.” And Yao found a task she could do herself; taking a pail and going outside. &lt;em&gt;How really considerate of Wanwan-senpai to quietly go with her&lt;/em&gt;, Maomao thought.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Other people set up the firewood, looked for seating to make up for the insufficient chairs, or did nothing and idled around.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Food was brought in a little while later.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;It was a soup made from vegetables and bear meat alongside a millet porridge. People were divided into two camps over the hearty and simple flavour based on preference.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“It’s a little bland.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I feel this much is perfect. I do have salt, though. Do you want some?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I do. Rather, your bosom pocket has everything, huh?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Give me some too, please.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Me too, me too.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I’m good with just the porridge.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“As expected, the meat stiiinks.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“If only I had brought ginger with me.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Dinner came to an end amidst the varied conversations.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao, Yao, and Changsha decided to sleep together in the smallest room. Although cramped, it contained a bed big enough for two people.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Furs enough for one person were laid out on the floor.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I will sleep on the floor,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“No, &lt;em&gt;I &lt;/em&gt;will,” Changsha said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Umm…” Yao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao suggested her sleep on the floor since she didn’t mind it, but Changsha found it unacceptable as a junior.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“There are furs, so don’t worry about it,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Likewise for you,” Changsha said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Umm…” Yao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;It was out of the question for Yao, the sheltered young lady, so Maomao and Changsha continued their discussion.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Umm… I can sleep on the floor,” Yao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Yao-san, you don’t have to worry about it,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Yes, what she said,” Changsha said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“But, two people are meant to sleep on the bed, right? What would happen if En’en were to hear of it?” Yao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;““…”” Maomao and Changsha exchanged glances.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Sorry, but may I sleep on the floor?” Yao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I&amp;#8217;m sorry…” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;This was the result of weighing between sleeping on the same bed as the young lady, and having her sleep on the floor. Either would incur wrath, but sharing a bed with her would put their lives in danger.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Yes! I will be sleeping on the floor!” Yao was oddly proud about it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;sup&gt;T/N: Happy New Year!&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right wp-block-paragraph"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/15-07-baby-deer-baby-boar-baby-bear-3/"&gt;Next Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/15-06-baby-deer-baby-boar-baby-bear-2/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-5623-6a4690edb8152' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20260702#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=5623&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-5623-6a4690edb8152' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-5623-6a4690edb8152' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=