    <item>
      <title>SS: Skyscraper</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/ss-skyscraper/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/ss-skyscraper/</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 23 Mar 2026 09:33:40 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main id="wp--skip-link--target" class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;SS: Skyscraper&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;sup&gt;T/N: This short story is based on the light novel continuity, referencing an event that happened in LN2. I don&amp;#8217;t know what the official translation of the tower where Jinshi performed his ritual thing is, but just know it&amp;#8217;s the same place.&lt;/sup&gt; &lt;sup&gt;Literally, it&amp;#8217;s the fancy word for &amp;#8220;sky&amp;#8221; and then &amp;#8220;altar&amp;#8221;, hence me translating it as &amp;#8220;Sky Altar&amp;#8221; for brevity.&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao looked outside in a daze.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;She was at A’duo’s palace. The view from the third-storey window was quite grand.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I wonder what she wants me here for today,” she said while drinking the tea she was served.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;It was at the end of the workday, so the sun had mostly set. Instead of a full moon, she could only see a few stars scattered across the sky. In turn, the lights from the pleasure district to the north were in clear view.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;It’s quite late, so she must have prepared a meal for me at least.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao waited quietly with a hope that bordered on certainty.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;A’duo would surely bring in a bottle of wine and serve out generous portions of meat and fish. After a long day of work, Maomao was in the mood for strongly seasoned meat.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;There was the sound of someone coming up the stairs.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao’s eyes sparkled with anticipation.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I’ve kept you waiting.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;What came wasn’t fragrantly grilled meat nor steaming soup, but a nobleman who exuded a refined fragrance.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Jinshi. He came in alone. The guards waited outside the room.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“&amp;#8230;what’s with your expression?” he asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“What do you mean by that?” she said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“You look disappointed.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“You must be imagining things.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“It didn’t look like I imagined it.” Jinshi sullenly sat down beside Maomao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;She was going to stand up in response, but stayed seated when he stopped her with his hand.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Did A’duo-sama invite you?” she asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Yeah, she told me she got her hands on some interesting wine.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“So, it’s wine?!” Maomao’s eyes shone.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Jinshi narrowed his eyes at her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“So it’s wine again, I see.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Looks like the appetisers have come before the wine,” he remarked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Servants had appeared to set down food in front of the two of them.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;As Maomao expected, it was a spread of richly flavoured meat dishes. The meat, grilled to fragrant crispiness, garnished with condiments, stimulated her appetite.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Before you partake in your meal, allow me.” One servant remained behind while the other left the room.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I don’t need a food taster,” Jinshi said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Understood,” the remaining servant said, then also left the room.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao had already picked up the silver chopsticks.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“You’re such an enthusiastic food taster,” he said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Yes, excuse me.” Maomao, using the chopsticks, carefully dished out a portion of the side dishes onto a plate. The reason she took samples from several places instead of just one was that no one could know where it could be poisoned. Of course, A’duo wouldn’t do such a thing as serve poison, but Maomao had to stick to the usual procedures.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;With a wide smile, she stuffed her cheeks with meat.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;This is so, so good.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;If she had some soft bread, she could sandwich the meat in between with some condiments, and it would be absolutely delicious. She wanted to sink her teeth in after it soaked up the sauce rich with savoury meat flavour.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;However, even A’duo’s palace had to pay attention to the meal served to the imperial brother. Instead of bread, there was a seafood congee made from high-class ingredients.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;This is delicious too, but I feel like eating bread today.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Not like she could call for the servants to make some for her. Maomao tasted the congee as well.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Food tasting is complete,’ she said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Mhm.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao set the plate before Jinshi.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Jinshi picked up his chopstick and ate it all up. He ate quickly thanks to his age, physique, and enviable stamina. Though he ate quickly, it didn’t spoil his elegance, perhaps a testament to his cultivated bearing.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Would you like seconds?” she asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Yes.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao filled a fresh bowl of congee, then looked out the window again.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“What’s wrong?” he asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Nothing, I was just thinking that you can see a lot from a tall building. I also saw a lot from the outer wall of the inner palace, though.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“There’s a place where you can see even more. Shall I show you next time?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“It sounds like a place that would be quite hard to get into, so there is no need for that.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“You should’ve jumped at the chance,” Jinshi said as he used a soup spoon to scoop up some congee.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Would the tallest building in the imperial court be the Sky Altar?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;It was where Jinshi’s life had been threatened during a rite.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Mmm, I wonder. That being said, I once read in the records that there had been a building even taller than that before the capital was relocated.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“A building even taller than the Sky Altar?” Maomao immediately caught on.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Apparently, it was a tower made of nine roofs stacked on top of each other. The height was said to be nearly thirty &lt;em&gt;jou &lt;/em&gt;(90m).”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Ohh? So they could build a building that tall.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Jinshi waved his fingers in explanation. “Yeah, apparently it had been designed with precise calculations. Someone like Rahan would be interested.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao pretended she didn’t hear the name Rahan.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I heard the emperor at the time had ordered a tower tall enough to scrape the sky to be built,” he added.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“As expected of heavenly people. The things they do are grand in scale.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Such ambition.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“So they couldn’t construct a building that surpassed it when they relocated the capital,” she said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“The ninefold tower had been destroyed by lightning.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Ahhh,” Maomao got it. “Lightning struck it because it was that tall.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Yeah, moreover, the top of the tower was decorated with a metal &lt;em&gt;fenghuang&lt;/em&gt;.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“It would have been stranger if it hadn’t been struck.” Convinced, Maomao went for more of the side dishes. She really wanted some bread.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I think, with current technology, we could build a much taller tower, but there’s nothing we can do about lightning.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“It’s a natural phenomenon after all.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;That being said, what kind of view could be seen from a tower that exceeded thirty &lt;em&gt;jou&lt;/em&gt;? Surely a view of dozens of &lt;em&gt;ri &lt;/em&gt;into the distance would be possible?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao’s imagination couldn’t fathom the kind of view.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Sorry for making you wait.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;A’duo showed up. She was holding onto a strangely-shaped container made of pale glass. “The children wouldn’t fall asleep.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;She set the container on the table. It was shaped like the tower they had been talking about earlier.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“It is in the shape of the tower that scraped the sky, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Oh, you can tell the design?” A’duo looked Maomao, impressed. “This bottle, you see, was created with the idea of a tower that pierced through the clouds in mind. An eccentric person brought it over to have me invest in it, but he asked the wrong person. Nonetheless, such a beautiful glass is quite rare, so I tried inviting some guests over.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Then, wouldn’t it be better to invite his imperial majesty instead?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Hahaha, do you want them to be a purveyor to the imperial household?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao thought that summoning Jinshi was similar, but summoning Jinshi &lt;em&gt;was &lt;/em&gt;easier than summoning the emperor.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Why did you call for me?” Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“You don’t like wine?” A&amp;#8217;duo asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Don’t be absurd.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I heard that there is a fellow among Maomao’s relatives who would be into this sort of modelled object.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;It would be difficult to ignore the name Rahan this time.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“The container may be the main topic, but I’ve prepared a good wine inside. Drink up.” A’duo heartily poured wine with one hand. The contents seem to be a pale green grape wine.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“Can you connect her to Rahan?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;“I think he will jump at the chance.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;Maomao had a short exchange with Jinshi, then accepted the cup passed to her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;While wondering when the day a tower like this glass bottle would be built in the passing of time&amp;#8230;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;sup&gt;T/N: I&amp;#8217;ll throw in a note later about where this short story came from when I have some extra time.&lt;/sup&gt; &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="wp-block-paragraph"&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/ss-skyscraper/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-5646-6a467fbee1c85' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20260702#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=5646&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-5646-6a467fbee1c85' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-5646-6a467fbee1c85' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/ss-skyscraper/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
